yuna: Two weeks.
yuna: That's how long I've spent in this city —
yuna: — and I still don't fully understand how Baku operates.
yuna: She has no patrol schedule.
yuna: No documentation system.
yuna: No protocol of any kind that I can study and follow.
yuna: She notices things before I do. Always.
yuna: But only if I look myself — she won't just tell me.
yuna: "You'll understand it better if you see it," she says. Every time.
yuna: It's infuriating.
yuna: It also works, which makes it more infuriating.
yuna: The strangest part isn't how she operates. It's that I still don't know who she is.
yuna: No last name. No association record.
yuna: No explanation for how a teenager ended up alone in a city full of monsters and is somehow completely fine with that.
yuna: I've heard rumors, once, when I was small. About a witch who drove every monster back to this city alone.
yuna: Singlehandedly ended the apocalypse.
yuna: Nobody knew her name. Nobody knew where she went after.
yuna: I used to think about that a lot.
yuna: I've been thinking about it again lately.
